 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udesbarolis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Desbarolis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 392<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/26/01 9:20:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What to look for</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> you know what people expect? A lot of neat flashing icons. You could be singing jig o vigor and they wouldnt care. Just give them icons to stare at. And dont die. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
LOL!  Man, that has to be the funniest thing I've read in awhile.  If I wasn't at work I'd prawly still be rolling on the floor.<br>
<br>
/me picks himself up off the floor.<br>
<br>
Ok, anyway.  Uhh, I think I have to agree with Trev here.  Best thing I've seen bards do is regen, and #2 damage shields.  What class, really, can top a bard for damage shields?  Mages, that's who.  And they'd have to have the staff from VP that summons lava diamonds in order to do it.  Even then, it's a close one.<br>
<br>
Any cleric willing to get upset at the bard for not playing mana song, when they are helping the rest of the group to be able to kill something fast enough that the cleric doesn't need to heal as much ... is a dumb cleric.  A bard should know his or her place well enough to know what to do, and when to do it.  They don't need the cleric dictating that to them.<br>
<br>
Just do the math sometime.  Using Analorne as an example, she adds 7 mana per tick regen, if all she does is that one song.  Twist it in every once in awhile (as most people tell you to do), and your getting around 2.5 mana per tick.  But, just for the sake of discussion, we'll say the bard plays it straight through.<br>
<br>
Clerics at around level 50-55 have 3 pretty efficient healing spells.  Remedy, Celestial Heal, and Complete Heal.  Remedy heals at a rate of 2.5hp per mana point, celestial heal is 3.2, and complete heal ranges from 3.2 - 13+ -- depending on who they are healing.<br>
<br>
Now if you figure that the bard is providing 7 mana per tick, they are effectively providing 22-50 hp regen -- again, depending on who is being healed, and how much they are being healed for.  Typically speaking, in *most* situations, the main tank being healed has 3000-3500hp in your average group situation, and the cleric usually cheals (in most situations I've seen) when the main tank hits about 30% life, so they are being healed for roughly 2200 damage under most situations.  2200 / 400 (cheal costs 400 mana) = 5.5hp per mana point.  If the bard were providing *just* mana, and nothing else (they would have to in order to provide 7 mana per tick pre-lvl 55), the bard is effectively providing 38hp of regen, which would be used later on down the road.<br>
<br>
Now a lvl 50 bard playing their lower level regen, and nivs melody of preservation with just a storebought lute provides 34hp regen -- per person.  Remember that if the bard is doing their job, during a fight they should be twisting songs and/or doing crowd control.  In a best case scenario you might get 7 mana outta that bard every 15 seconds (or about 4 times a minute).  Of course if you don't mind the bard doing jack but swinging their weapons and singing that stupid song, be my guest.  Just don't ask me to join your group.<br>
<br>
Take that level 50 bard who's providing 34hp regen, and hand them either maestro's lute or a lute of the howler, and it becomes 41hp regen.  Myself at 56, I'm doing 47hp (not to mention 12 mana per tick, which if the cleric alone were accounted for, is then increasing the amount of health I'm providing to the group by anywhere from 30-70hp per tick).<br>
<br>
Now if that wasn't good enough for you, consider how many people in the group are injured.  Every one of those people in the group is receiving that regeneration.  So using the lowest number there, 34hp, if you figure just two people are injured, that doubles to 68.  3 people is 102.  4 is 136, 5 is 170, and 6 is 204.  204hp regen per tick.  Name a cleric who can top that with any bard who's providing 7 mana regen (from the bard alone, you can't include your own natural regen or clarity because that skews the issue at hand).  Now use the higher number.  6 * 47 = 282.  282 + 50 (I'm giving 12 mana, remember?) = 332.<br>
<br>
You'd have to have a healing spell capable of providing 29 hp per mana point to pull off the 204hp, which even complete heal can't do if it were being used to it's fullest potential (cheal actually heals 10,000 damage, rather than healing the target completely, and 29 * 400 = 11,600hp).  40hp per mana point to top the lvl 56 bard with lute of the howler.<br>
<br>
Post 55, you want mana?  Great, I'll gladly provide you mana, thank god you can't bitch while I do what I actually am good at doing, and when you do whine I can make you look like a fool.  Just sit your ass down and waggle your finger a few times when the situation warrants it, meanwhile I'll continue to swing my weapons and strum my lute.<br>
<br>
-Desbarolis -- 56th Mana Bitch <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uqumaden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qumaden</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://qumaden.homestead.com/files/Mog_walk.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 686<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/26/01 9:27:42 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://qumaden.homestead.com/files/bengali.gif height=85 width=85></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What to look for</span><hr size=1> I look for lambent. <p><center><a href=" http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5053"><img src="http://qumaden.homestead.com/files/sig1113.jpg"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=7504.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showMessage?topicID=7524.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showMessage?topicID=7518.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=7504.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.threadControl?topicID=7504.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7504.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.unsubscribeUnr